file=Cybersecurity/veil/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: veil-logical-book-requirements\ntype: logical\nstatus: built — 1 dedicated script + inherits from Shared OS (2026-07-14)\nassigned_agent: veil (Cybersecurity / Privacy & Data Protection)\ndate_added: 2026-07-09\ndate_filled: 2026-07-14\n · p:=Logical artifacts are Python scripts in `Shared OS/logical/` (playbook §13.5). Veil owns 1 dedicated script for privacy compliance and inherits cross-agent scripts. This file is the only file in this folder.\n · tb=\| # \| Script \| Source Book 1 \| Book 1 URL \| Source Book 2 \| Book 2 URL \| Route \| · tb=\|---\|--------\|--------------\|------------\|---------------\|------------\|-------\| · tb=\| 1 \| `privacy_compliance.py` \| NIST, *Privacy Framework v1.0* (2020) \| [nvlpubs.nist.gov](https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/CSWP/NIST.CSWP.01162020.pdf) — FREE \| GDPR, Regulation (EU) 2016/679 \| [eur-lex.europa.eu](https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/reg/2016/679/oj) — FREE \| B \| · tb=\| Script \| Source Book \| Book URL \| Why Veil Needs It \| · tb=\|--------\|------------\|----------\|---------------------\| · tb=\| `risk_management.py` \| NIST SP 800-30 + SP 800-37 \| [csrc.nist.gov](https://csrc.nist.gov/) \| DLP alert severity feeds risk register; data classification \| · tb=\| `incident_response.py` \| NIST SP 800-61r2 + SP 800-40r4 \| [csrc.nist.gov](https://csrc.nist.gov/) \| Breach notification integrates with IR workflow \| · tb=\| `identity_zero_trust.py` \| NIST SP 800-207 + SP 800-63-3 \| [csrc.nist.gov](https://csrc.nist.gov/) \| Data access control and privacy-sensitive authentication \| · tb=\| Previously Flagged (0.6) \| Status \| Script \| · tb=\|--------------------------\|--------\|--------\| · tb=\| Classification decision tree (4-tier model — qualitative) \| ✅ Cleared \| `privacy_compliance.py` (classify_data per NIST PF + GDPR Art. 5) \| · tb=\| DLP alert severity thresholds (rubric-based) \| ✅ Cleared \| `privacy_compliance.py` (dlp_alert_severity per NIST PF Protect-P) \| · tb=\| Notification clock estimates (GDPR 72h vs PIPEDA "as feasible") \| ✅ Cleared \| `privacy_compliance.py` (breach_notification_clock per GDPR Art. 33-34) \| · sm:=- **data-classification** → imports `privacy_compliance.py` (classify_data) + `risk_management.py` (asset_criticality_weight)\n- **breach-notification** → imports `privacy_compliance.py` (breach_notification_clock, dpia_required) + `incident_response.py` (incident_severity)\n- **dlp-monitoring** → imports `privacy_compliance.py` (dlp_alert_severity)\n